      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "client_secret[\"'\\s]*[:=][\"'\\s]*([A-Za-z0-9_-]{40,80})",
        "message": "Okta OIDC client secret detected in configuration. Client secrets are credentials used by applications to authenticate with Okta's OIDC/OAuth2 endpoints. Exposing these in source code enables attackers to impersonate your application, obtain unauthorized access tokens, and compromise user authentication flows. Use secure credential storage such as environment variables or secret management systems.",
